Interface ValueChooserEditor<V>

  • Type Parameters:
    V - the value type.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Component, Editable, java.lang.Iterable<Component>, LocaleContextSource, ValueEditor<V>

    public interface ValueChooserEditor<V>
extends ValueEditor<V>
    A value editor that allows the selection of a value - not necessarily modification.
    Author:
    Russ Tennant (russ@proteus.co)

      • setValueChooserDisplayHandler

        void setValueChooserDisplayHandler(@Nullable
                                   ValueChooserDisplayHandler<V> handler)
        Set the handler to receive notification when the user wishes to choose a different value.

        If a handler is not set, implementations will provide a default presentation of the chooser.

        Parameters:
        handler - the listener.
